@startuml class_diagram

title Calculator — Class Diagram

package "src" {
    class Calculator {
        {static} logger : Logger
        {static} UNARY_OPS : set
        {static} BINARY_OPS : set
        {static} INTEGER_OPS : set
        {static} SCIENTIFIC_UNARY_OPS : set
        +history : list[dict]
        +__init__()
        +get_history() : list[dict]
        +add(a, b) : number
        +subtract(a, b) : number
        +multiply(a, b) : number
        +divide(a, b) : number
        +factorial(n) : int
        +square(n) : number
        +cube(n) : number
        +square_root(n) : float
        +cube_root(n) : float
        +power(base, exp) : number
        +log(n) : float
        +ln(n) : float
        +sin(x) : float
        +cos(x) : float
        +tan(x) : float
        +asin(x) : float
        +acos(x) : float
        +atan(x) : float
        +sinh(x) : float
        +cosh(x) : float
        +tanh(x) : float
        +exp(x) : float
        +execute(op: str, *operands: float|int) : float|int
        -{static} _to_int_if_needed(op: str, value: float) : float | int
    }

    class "__main__" as Main <<module>> {
        {static} logger : Logger
        +MAX_INPUT_ATTEMPTS : int
        +MENU : str
        +MENU_MAP : dict[str, str]
        +SCIENTIFIC_MENU : str
        +SCIENTIFIC_MENU_MAP : dict[str, str]
        +parse_number(prompt: str, max_attempts: int) : float
        +run_operation(calc: Calculator, op: str) : void
        -_format_result(value: int | float) : str
        -_show_history(calc: Calculator) : void
        +cli_main(args: list) : int
        +main() : void
    }

    class CalculatorGUI {
        {static} logger : Logger
        +root : tk.Tk
        +calc : Calculator
        +mode : str
        +expression_var : StringVar
        +display_var : StringVar
        +sci_frame : Frame
        -_pending_op : str | None
        -_first_operand : float | None
        -_current_input : str
        +__init__(root: tk.Tk)
        -_build_ui() : void
        +press_digit(digit: str) : void
        +clear() : void
        +set_binary_op(op: str) : void
        +equals() : void
        +execute_unary(op: str) : void
        +toggle_mode() : void
        +show_history() : void
        +{static} _format(value: int | float) : str
    }

    class "gui" as GUIMod <<module>> {
        +launch_gui() : void
    }
}

package "src.operations" {
    class "arithmetic" <<module>> {
        +add(a, b) : float|int
        +subtract(a, b) : float|int
        +multiply(a, b) : float|int
        +divide(a, b) : float
    }

    class "advanced" <<module>> {
        +factorial(n: int) : int
        +square(n) : float|int
        +cube(n) : float|int
        +square_root(n) : float
        +cube_root(n) : float
        +power(base, exp) : float|int
        +log(n) : float
        +ln(n) : float
    }

    class "scientific" <<module>> {
        +sin(x) : float
        +cos(x) : float
        +tan(x) : float
        +asin(x) : float
        +acos(x) : float
        +atan(x) : float
        +sinh(x) : float
        +cosh(x) : float
        +tanh(x) : float
        +exp(x) : float
    }
}

Main ..> Calculator : instantiates / dispatches via calc.execute(op, ...)
Main ..> GUIMod : lazy import when sys.argv[1] == "--gui"
GUIMod ..> CalculatorGUI : instantiates in launch_gui()
CalculatorGUI *-- Calculator : owns (self.calc = Calculator())
Calculator ..> arithmetic : delegates add/subtract/multiply/divide
Calculator ..> advanced : delegates factorial/square/cube/\nsquare_root/cube_root/power/log/ln
Calculator ..> scientific : delegates sin/cos/tan/asin/acos/\natan/sinh/cosh/tanh/exp
CalculatorGUI ..> Calculator : all ops via calc.execute()

note right of Calculator::logger
  logging.getLogger(__name__).
  Used by divide, factorial,
  square_root, log, ln, asin,
  and acos to log at ERROR level
  before re-raising.
end note

note right of Calculator::UNARY_OPS
  Module-level constants in calculator.py.
  UNARY_OPS: {"factorial","square","cube",
    "square_root","cube_root","log","ln"}
  BINARY_OPS: {"add","subtract","multiply",
    "divide","power"}
  INTEGER_OPS: {"factorial"}
  SCIENTIFIC_UNARY_OPS: {"sin","cos","tan",
    "asin","acos","atan","sinh","cosh","tanh","exp"}
  SCIENTIFIC_UNARY_OPS is disjoint from UNARY_OPS.
  __main__ imports all four sets.
end note

note right of Calculator::history
  Per-instance history list.
  Entries: {"op": str, "operands": tuple, "result": float|int}.
  Appended by execute() on success;
  failed operations are not recorded.
  get_history() returns a shallow copy.
end note

note right of Calculator::execute
  Dispatches by op name via getattr(self, op).
  For BINARY_OPS: unpacks two operands.
  For UNARY_OPS: calls _to_int_if_needed first
    (coerces to int for INTEGER_OPS; raises
    ValueError for non-whole numbers).
  For SCIENTIFIC_UNARY_OPS: passes operand directly
    (no int coercion needed).
  Appends history entry on success.
  Raises ValueError for unknown ops.
  Propagates ZeroDivisionError/ValueError unchanged.
end note

note right of Calculator::_to_int_if_needed
  Module-level helper in calculator.py.
  If op not in INTEGER_OPS, returns value unchanged.
  If value is a whole number, returns int(value).
  Otherwise raises ValueError.
end note

note right of Calculator::divide
  Raises ZeroDivisionError when b == 0.
  Logs "divide error: division by zero"
  at ERROR level before re-raising.
  Delegates to arithmetic.divide(a, b).
end note

note right of Calculator::factorial
  Delegates to advanced.factorial(n)
  which calls math.factorial(n).
  Raises ValueError for n < 0.
  Logs error at ERROR level before re-raising.
end note

note right of Calculator::square_root
  Delegates to advanced.square_root(n)
  which calls math.sqrt(n).
  Raises ValueError for n < 0.
  Logs error at ERROR level before re-raising.
end note

note right of Calculator::cube_root
  Delegates to advanced.cube_root(n)
  which calls math.cbrt(n).
  Handles negative inputs.
  Requires Python 3.11+
end note

note right of Calculator::log
  Delegates to advanced.log(n)
  which calls math.log10(n).
  Raises ValueError for n <= 0.
  Logs error at ERROR level before re-raising.
end note

note right of Calculator::ln
  Delegates to advanced.ln(n)
  which calls math.log(n).
  Raises ValueError for n <= 0.
  Logs error at ERROR level before re-raising.
end note

note right of Calculator::asin
  Delegates to scientific.asin(x)
  which calls math.asin(x).
  Raises ValueError for |x| > 1.
  Logs error at ERROR level before re-raising.
end note

note right of Calculator::acos
  Delegates to scientific.acos(x)
  which calls math.acos(x).
  Raises ValueError for |x| > 1.
  Logs error at ERROR level before re-raising.
end note

note left of Main::logger
  logging.getLogger(__name__).
  Used by run_operation and cli_main
  to log caught errors at ERROR level.
  main() configures logging.basicConfig
  (level=ERROR) before any dispatch.
end note

note left of Main::main
  Checks sys.argv[1] == "--gui" first.
  If matched: lazy-imports src.gui.launch_gui
  and calls it (GUI mode), then returns.
  Other argv: delegates to cli_main, then sys.exit.
  No argv: starts interactive REPL loop.
  REPL tracks mode ("normal"|"scientific");
  'h' shows history, 'm' toggles mode, 'q' quits.
end note

note left of Main::MENU_MAP
  Maps "1"–"12" to operation names.
  "h" shows history; "m" switches mode; "q" quits.
  All three handled directly in main().
end note

note left of Main::SCIENTIFIC_MENU_MAP
  Maps "1"–"10" to scientific op names:
  sin, cos, tan, asin, acos, atan,
  sinh, cosh, tanh, exp.
  Active when mode == "scientific".
  "m" switches back to normal mode.
end note

note left of Main::MAX_INPUT_ATTEMPTS
  Default = 3. parse_number retries
  up to max_attempts times; raises
  ValueError after all attempts fail.
  Remaining count printed on each
  invalid entry.
end note

note left of Main::run_operation
  Checks BINARY_OPS (imported from calculator)
  to decide operand count; UNARY_OPS and
  SCIENTIFIC_UNARY_OPS both take one operand.
  Calls calc.execute().
  Catches ValueError / ZeroDivisionError;
  logs via logger.error before printing
  "Error: ..." to stdout.
  REPL loop continues after errors.
end note

note left of Main::cli_main
  Parses sys.argv[1:] as
  <operation> [operands...]
  Uses all_ops = UNARY_OPS | BINARY_OPS | SCIENTIFIC_UNARY_OPS.
  Returns 0 on success, 1 on error.
  Logs errors via logger.error.
end note

note left of Main::_format_result
  Whole floats shown as integers
  (7.0 → "7"); fractional and
  int values pass through as-is
end note

note left of Main::_show_history
  Prints numbered entries:
  op(operands) = result
  or "No history yet." if empty
end note

note right of CalculatorGUI::__init__
  Attaches to tk.Tk root window.
  Creates owned Calculator instance (self.calc).
  Initialises: mode="normal", _pending_op=None,
  _first_operand=None, _current_input="".
  Calls _build_ui() to construct all widgets.
end note

note right of CalculatorGUI::_build_ui
  Lays out the full widget grid:
  row 0: display (expression_var + display_var labels)
  rows 1-4: digit buttons (0-9, .) + binary op buttons
  row 5: C, x², √, n! (clear + common unary ops)
  row 6: x³, ∛, log, ln (more unary ops)
  row 7: xʸ (power), Sci (toggle), Hist (history)
  row 8: sci_frame — 10 scientific op buttons
    (sin/cos/tan/asin/acos/atan/sinh/cosh/tanh/exp)
    hidden by default; shown when mode=="scientific"
end note

note right of CalculatorGUI::set_binary_op
  Stores float(_current_input) as _first_operand.
  Sets _pending_op to op name.
  Updates expression_var to show "operand op".
  Clears _current_input so user can type second operand.
  No-op if _current_input is empty.
end note

note right of CalculatorGUI::equals
  Executes calc.execute(_pending_op, _first_operand, b).
  On success: result becomes new _current_input;
    _pending_op and _first_operand reset to None.
  On ValueError/ZeroDivisionError: display shows
    "Error", expression shows exc message,
    _current_input cleared.
  No-op if _pending_op is None or input empty.
end note

note right of CalculatorGUI::execute_unary
  Executes calc.execute(op, float(_current_input)).
  Used for both normal unary ops (square, sqrt, etc.)
  and all 10 scientific ops (sin, cos, ..., exp).
  On success: result becomes new _current_input.
  On error: display shows "Error"; input cleared.
  No-op if _current_input is empty.
end note

note right of CalculatorGUI::toggle_mode
  Switches self.mode between "normal" and "scientific".
  "normal" → "scientific": sci_frame.grid() — panel shown.
  "scientific" → "normal": sci_frame.grid_remove() — hidden.
end note

note right of CalculatorGUI::show_history
  Calls calc.get_history().
  If empty: messagebox.showinfo "No history yet."
  Otherwise: numbered list of
    "op(operands) = result" via messagebox.showinfo.
end note

note right of GUIMod::launch_gui
  Module-level function in src/gui.py.
  Creates tk.Tk() root window.
  Instantiates CalculatorGUI(root).
  Calls root.mainloop() — blocks until window closed.
  Called by main() when sys.argv[1] == "--gui".
end note

note bottom of arithmetic
  Pure functions only; no state.
  divide raises ZeroDivisionError for b==0.
  Re-exported from src/operations/__init__.py.
end note

note bottom of advanced
  Pure functions; all delegate to math stdlib
  except square (n**2), cube (n**3), power (base**exp).
  Re-exported from src/operations/__init__.py.
end note

note bottom of scientific
  Pure functions; all delegate to math stdlib.
  All angle inputs/outputs in radians.
  asin/acos raise ValueError for |x| > 1.
  Re-exported from src/operations/__init__.py.
end note

@enduml
